New Year, New Skincare Goals! As we welcome a new year, let’s make taking care of our skin a top priority. My oily T- zone loves showing up places uninvited, especially when I have a full face of makeup. Nourishing our skin with the right products and self-care routine can make a huge difference in how we look and feel, with or without makeup.
 
The @Clarins CLEAR-OUT Purifying and Matifying Toner + RE-BOOST Matifying Blemish Gel are a duo that mattifies your skin while giving it the hydration it needs. I’m starting the year off right with products addressing my skincare concerns. Both products have a plant based healthy skin In & Out complex that works to keep your skin on the healthy path. 

The CLEAR-OUT Purifying and Matifying Toner is for all skin types. It is formulated with extracts that gently exfoliate to refine the skin’s texture.

The RE-BOOST Matifying Blemish Gel is made for combination and oily skin types. It has a formula that includes Meadowsweet extract & organic Strawberry tree fruit extract to help limit the overproduction of sebum. 
Cheers to a year of healthy, glowing skin!  #MyClarins

Another year, another trip around the sun 🌞 Today, I'm feeling especially grateful as I celebrate my birthday with all of you. Birthdays are always a time of reflection for me, and this year is no exception.

As I look back on the past year, I'm reminded of the challenges I've faced and the lessons I've learned. But I'm also reminded of the love and support that surrounds me every day, both online and off. Thank you to each and every one of you who make our online community a place of positivity, inspiration and fun. I couldn't do it without you!

Today is also a bittersweet day for me, as it's the day my dad was killed. But I choose to honor his memory by celebrating the fact that he gave me life not once, but twice. When I was born, I wasn't breathing, but my dad didn't hesitate to jump into action and give me mouth-to-mouth. His act of love has always stayed with me, and I'm reminded of it every year on my birthday.

As I enter another year of life, I'm committed to embracing the journey ahead with an open heart and an open mind. Life is long but goes by too quick to waste on anything but what truly matters, and I'm grateful for each and every moment. Sip, sip, hooray to another year of growth, adventure, and love! Happy Birthday to me! 🎉✨🎂 

SB: What do you think of my self-shot birthday shoot from yesterday? 😊 I have to admit, I didn’t think I’d pull it off but y’all were hyping me up in the DMs. I'm pretty happy with how it turned out!

SAVE FOR LATER📌 Where To Eat In Calgary: @lonelymouthbar on @17thavesw.

Patio season is upon us, and I know y’all are on the hunt for the perfect dining spot. Look no further than Lonely Mouth Bar! 😎🍽️

Here’s what I ordered:
🥝 Kiwi Slushie - $15: This refreshing drink is like a tropical vacation in a glass! Perfect for cooling down on those hot summer days. 🌴🍹
🐟 Bluefin Tuna Tartare - $19: A true delicacy! The freshness of the tuna combined with the miso emulsion will make your taste buds sing. 🎵🐠
🥦 Brussels Sprouts - $13: Who knew brussels sprouts could be so addictive? These crispy bites with a hint of sweetness from the bull dog sauce are an absolute must-try. Trust me, you won’t be able to resist going back for more! 🙌🏼🥦
🍣 Hand Rolls - $6.5/$7 ($4 during happy hour): These little bites of heaven are perfect for sushi lovers! Fresh ingredients, expertly rolled, and bursting with flavor. Don’t miss out on the happy hour deal to score these at a steal! 🎉🍣
🐟 Miso Cod - $37: Treat yourself to a dish fit for royalty. The miso-glazed cod is so tender and flavorful, it practically melts in your mouth. It’s a splurge-worthy indulgence that you won’t regret. 👑🐟
So, add Lonely Mouth Bar to your must-visit list and prepare yourself for a culinary adventure like no other! Your taste buds will thank you. 😉👌🏾

You know that saying we’ve all heard “it’s not a fashion show” .. I hate it! It’s so weird that people are bothered by the effort someone else puts into their own appearance.

I love that social media has normalized that so many of us enjoy the planning and getting ready process more than the actual event (sometimes😉😅). 

The time that it takes me to get ready gives me the chance to hype myself up before being a roomful of people I don’t know. Random fact I’m naturally a shy person in new spaces so my get ready time allows me that time to get rid of the butterflies and give myself a pep talk. Which is why I like getting ready alone 🙃. Cheers to being outside all Summer ✨
